06111nam a22007695i 9783868599114DE-B159720240306015011.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20142014gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97838685991147 a10.1515/97838685991142doi  a(DE-B1597)575708  a(OCoLC)1412008389  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aNA2750 7aARC0000002bisacsh04a004.01a004.01/511 aSchönwandt, Walter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSolving Complex Problems :bA Handbook /cWalter Schönwandt, Katrin Voermanek, Jürgen Utz, Jens Grunau, Christoph Hemberger. 1aBerlin : bJOVIS, c[2014] 4c©2014  a1 online resource (192 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- t0 Preface -- tProblems First? -- tWhy another handbook? -- t1 Deficient states -- tProblems First! -- tNo solution? No problem! -- tWhat do we mean by complexity? -- tThe constituent parts of a problem -- tThe deficient state A[-] -- tThe target state B[+] -- tThe unknown measures M? -- tShifting problems -- tConclusion -- tWorking aid -- t2 Mechanisms of action and propositions -- tA map of solutions -- tThe interrelation between causes and measures during problem-solving -- tA note on the issue of causality -- tCause – measure – consequences – assessment -- tA useful working aid: the map of solutions -- tPractical guidelines for the map of solutions -- tAn example of implementation: plastic waste -- tThe bundle of measures -- tWorking aids/possible error sources -- tConclusion0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWer Großes plant, steht schnell vor Problemen – tagtäglich hören wir davon. Je größer das Projekt, je komplexer die Aufgabe, desto mehr hat man es mit diffizilen, multidisziplinären Aufgabenstellungen zu tun. Häufige Aufgabe der Architektur, Stadt- und Raumplanung – aber auch der Politik sowie jeder Art von Organisation, ob Behörde oder Unternehmen – ist es, funktionierende Lösungen für solche Herausforderungen zu liefern. Und genau dabei hilft dieses Buch! Es vermittelt eine Methodik zur gezielten, systematischen, problem- und handlungsorientierten Entwicklung von Lösungen. Dabei wird über Disziplingrenzen hinweg Wissen generiert, Wert- und Interessenskonflikte werden in den Lösungsprozess integriert. Nur wenn man genau weiß, wo man anpacken und worauf man achten muss, wird das Lösen komplexer Probleme machbar und erfolgreich. Dieses Buch richtet sich an Architekten, Stadt- und Raumplaner, aber ebenso an Politiker und Manager – schließlich stehen sie alle immer wieder vor der Aufgabe, komplexe multidisziplinäre Problemstellungen bearbeiten zu müs-sen, denen mit Routinelösungen nicht beizukommen ist, wohl aber mit der in diesem Handbuch beschriebenen Problemlösungssystematik.  aWhen you’re planning something big, problems appear rather quickly. We hear of them on a daily basis. The bigger or more complex a task, the more we have to deal with complicated, multidisciplinary task formulations. In many cases it is architecture, including urban and spatial planning, but also politics and all types of organizational forms, irrespective of whether they are public authorities or private enterprises, which are expected to deliver functional solutions for such challenges. This is precisely where this book is helpful. It introduces a methodology for developing target-specific, systematic and problem-oriented as well as action-oriented solutions. In doing so, knowledge is created that goes beyond discipline limits while conflicts of values and of interests are integrated into the solution process. Only if one knows exactly where to start and what must be borne in mind is the task of solving complex problems doable and ultimately successful. This book is addressed to architects as well as to urban and spatial planners, and likewise to politicians and managers. After all, all these different professionals are repeatedly confronted with the task of handling complex, multidisciplinary problems which cannot be solved by applying routine solutions but, indeed, can be successfully addressed by applying the problem-solving system described in this book.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aOrganisation. 4aPlanung. 4aProblemlösung. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  aAufgabenstellung.  aEntwicklung.  aLösung.  aLösungsprozess.  aProblembeschreibung.  amultidisziplinäre Aufgaben.1 aHemberger, Christoph, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aUtz, Jürgen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVoermanek, Katrin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cprintz978386859244340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978386859911440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783868599114423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783868599114/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles